The connection between decisions: D1 creates the component boundaries. D2 decides what lives
inside each boundary. D3 decides how the boundaries are connected at runtime. Remove any one of
the three and the architecture degrades: no D1 means no testable isolation, no D2 means
unmaintainable use case classes, no D3 means wiring leaks everywhere.